Step 1: Install Conda3 
Step 2: Install conda-mirror
        conda install -c conda-forge  conda-mirror
Step 3: Create a conf.yaml conf file so that it can pull package according to your need specified in that configuration file.(attached withit).
Step 4: Dry run to check your package available or not.
        conda-mirror --upstream-channel main --target-directory /home/vm/Music/Conda/ --config /home/vm/conf.yaml --dry-run --platform linux-64 -vv
Step 5: Directly download all package from the official mirror without using conf.yaml file using following command.
        conda-mirror --upstream-channel main --target-directory /home/vm/Music/Conda/ --platform linux-64 -vv
Step 6: Download package using conf.yaml file with the following command.
        conda-mirror --upstream-channel main --target-directory /home/vm/Music/Conda/ --platform linux-64 -vv
